  <!-- Tab: Backend -->
  <div class="tab-content" id="tab-backend">
    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>The backend is an <strong>Express.js</strong> API server that acts as a middleware layer between the React frontend and <strong>Directus</strong> (headless CMS). Instead of exposing Directus directly to the client, all requests pass through this Express server, which adds:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Authentication</strong> with JWT access/refresh tokens and bcrypt password hashing</li>
        <li><strong>Role-based access control</strong> for admin and teacher roles</li>
        <li><strong>Business logic</strong> — grade computation (50/50 exam/CA split), position ranking, PDF report generation</li>
        <li><strong>Data normalization</strong> — transforms Directus responses into consistent frontend-friendly shapes</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>How to Run</h2>
      <pre><code>cd backend
npm install
cp ../.env .          # ensure DIRECTUS_TOKEN and JWT_SECRET are set
npm run dev           # nodemon, hot-reload on port 9002</code></pre>
      <p>Requires <code>DIRECTUS_URL</code> and <code>DIRECTUS_TOKEN</code> in the environment (Directus must be running).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Folder Structure</h2>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>app.js</h4>
        <p>Express app entry point. Registers global middleware (Helmet, CORS, Morgan, CookieParser, JSON parser), mounts route modules under <code>/api/</code>, serves docs routes at <code>/</code> and <code>/docs</code>, and defines global 404/500 error handlers. Configures EJS view engine and static file serving for <code>/public</code>. Listens on the configured port.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>config/index.js</h4>
        <p>Loads environment variables via <code>dotenv</code>. Exposes a typed config object for port, CORS origin, Directus URL/token, JWT secret/expiry. Validates that required keys (<code>DIRECTUS_TOKEN</code>, <code>JWT_SECRET</code>) are present at startup — the server will crash with a clear message if they are missing.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>controllers/</h4>
        <p>Each resource has a dedicated controller file. Controllers receive <code>(req, res)</code>, extract query parameters / body / route params, call Directus via services, apply business logic, and return JSON responses (or PDF streams).</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>auth.controller.js</strong> — Login, register, refresh tokens, profile CRUD, user management (admin). Uses bcrypt for password comparison, JWT for tokens. Writes system logs on signup/login.</li>
          <li><strong>students.controller.js</strong> — CRUD for students. Validates unique admission numbers. Scopes access by class for teachers.</li>
          <li><strong>assessments.controller.js</strong> — CRUD for exam/CA scores. Prevents duplicates, validates score limits, filters by type/term/year/class.</li>
          <li><strong>attendance.controller.js</strong> — Lists records, bulk upserts attendance, returns dates and aggregate stats.</li>
          <li><strong>classStreams.controller.js</strong> — CRUD for class streams with computed student counts.</li>
          <li><strong>subjects.controller.js</strong> — CRUD for subjects plus assign/unassign to class streams.</li>
          <li><strong>reports.controller.js</strong> — JSON and PDF report cards. 50/50 score split, per-subject positions, grading scale CRUD.</li>
          <li><strong>system.controller.js</strong> — Telemetry endpoint and logs viewer.</li>
          <li><strong>docs.controller.js</strong> — Renders EJS views for <code>/</code> and <code>/docs</code> with live Directus status.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>routes/</h4>
        <p>Thin route modules, one per resource. Each creates an <code>express.Router()</code>, applies auth middleware, maps methods + paths to controller functions. Routes are mounted in <code>app.js</code> under <code>/api/:resource</code>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>middleware/auth.js</h4>
        <p>JWT verification middleware. <code>authenticate</code> extracts Bearer token, verifies against <code>JWT_SECRET</code> and issuer, sets <code>req.user</code>. <code>authorize(...roles)</code> checks role. <code>requireRole(...)</code> chains both.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>services/directus.service.js</h4>
        <p>Axios-based client for Directus REST API. Exports CRUD helpers, handles parameter flattening, logs all requests.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>services/grades.js</h4>
        <p>Grading engine. Caches grading scales from Directus. <code>determineGrade</code> converts score to percentage and matches grade. <code>calculatePosition</code> implements standard competition ranking ("1224" style).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>services/pdf.js</h4>
        <p>PDF generation using <strong>PDFKit</strong>. <code>generateReportCard</code> creates styled A4 report card with brand-colored header, student info, subject table (with per-subject positions and color-coded grades), totals, and signature lines.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>views/ &amp; public/</h4>
        <p>EJS templates (<code>views/</code>) and static assets (<code>public/css</code>, <code>public/js</code>) for the documentation UI. Rendered by the docs controller with Lucide icons and dark theme matching the frontend.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Tech Decisions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Express over Fastify/NestJS</strong> — Lightweight, zero-config, vast ecosystem. The API surface is simple (CRUD + reports), so Express's simplicity is a strength.</li>
        <li><strong>Directus proxy pattern</strong> — Directus handles auth, data persistence, and admin panel. The Express server adds business logic (scoring, ranking, PDF generation) that Directus cannot express.</li>
        <li><strong>JWT over sessions</strong> — Stateless auth suitable for an SPA. Short-lived access tokens (15m) with longer-lived refresh tokens stored in localStorage.</li>
        <li><strong>PDFKit over Puppeteer</strong> — PDFKit generates PDFs programmatically without a browser. Lighter, faster, and simpler for structured report cards.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

