  <!-- Tab: Frontend -->
  <div class="tab-content" id="tab-frontend">
    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>The frontend is a <strong>React 18</strong> single-page application built with <strong>TypeScript</strong>, <strong>Vite</strong>, and <strong>Tailwind CSS</strong>. It communicates with the Express backend via a typed API client layer. The UI is organized into feature modules (assessments, attendance, reports, etc.), each with its own page component and API bindings.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>How to Run</h2>
      <pre><code>cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev           # Vite dev server on port 9001, proxies /api to :9002
npm run typecheck     # tsc --noEmit, catches type errors
npm run build         # production build</code></pre>
      <p>The Vite dev server proxies <code>/api/*</code> requests to the backend. For production, the built static files are served by an Nginx container.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Folder Structure</h2>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>App.tsx</h4>
        <p>Root component with React Router route definitions. Wraps authenticated routes in a <code>ProtectedRoute</code> component. Public routes: <code>/</code>, <code>/login</code>, <code>/signup</code>, <code>/approval</code>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>components/Layout.tsx</h4>
        <p>Main dashboard shell. Sticky sidebar with role-filtered navigation. Header with breadcrumb, mobile hamburger menu, and dark/light theme toggle.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>contexts/</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>AuthContext.tsx</strong> — Auth state management with localStorage persistence.</li>
          <li><strong>ThemeContext.tsx</strong> — Dark/light mode toggle with localStorage persistence.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>api/</h4>
        <p>Typed API client modules, one per resource. Each exports an interface and functions that call the corresponding backend endpoint via axios.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>client.ts</strong> — Base axios instance with auth interceptors.</li>
          <li><strong>auth.ts</strong> — Login, register, profile, user management.</li>
          <li><strong>students.ts</strong> — Student CRUD.</li>
          <li><strong>assessments.ts</strong> — Assessment CRUD.</li>
          <li><strong>attendance.ts</strong> — Attendance list, mark, dates, stats.</li>
          <li><strong>subjects.ts</strong> — Subject CRUD plus class assignment.</li>
          <li><strong>classStreams.ts</strong> — Class stream CRUD.</li>
          <li><strong>reports.ts</strong> — Grading scale CRUD, report JSON and PDF download.</li>
          <li><strong>system.ts</strong> — System status and logs.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="file-block">
        <h4>modules/</h4>
        <p>Self-contained feature modules with <code>pages/</code> directory and <code>index.ts</code> re-export.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>auth/</strong> — LoginPage, SignupPage, ApprovalPage, UserManagementPage</li>
          <li><strong>dashboard/</strong> — DashboardPage with stats, charts, quick actions</li>
          <li><strong>students/</strong> — StudentsPage, StudentDetailPage</li>
          <li><strong>class-streams/</strong> — ClassStreamsPage, ClassStreamDetailPage</li>
          <li><strong>subjects/</strong> — SubjectsPage with class assignment</li>
          <li><strong>assessments/</strong> — AssessmentsPage with filters and record form</li>
          <li><strong>attendance/</strong> — AttendancePage with bulk toggle and history</li>
          <li><strong>reports/</strong> — ReportsPage with class analysis and grading scales</li>
          <li><strong>system/</strong> — LogsPage with audit log viewer</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Tech Decisions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>React 18 over Vue/Svelte</strong> — Largest ecosystem, best TypeScript integration, most familiar to the team. React 18's automatic batching and concurrent features improve performance.</li>
        <li><strong>TypeScript over JavaScript</strong> — Catches type errors at compile time, provides self-documenting interfaces.</li>
        <li><strong>Vite over CRA/Next.js</strong> — Significantly faster dev (native ESM, instant HMR). No SSR requirement, so Next.js adds unnecessary complexity.</li>
        <li><strong>Tailwind CSS over CSS-in-JS</strong> — Utility-first approach reduces CSS bundle size, enforces design consistency, avoids runtime overhead.</li>
        <li><strong>TanStack Query over Redux</strong> — Automatic caching, background refetching, request deduplication. Reduces boilerplate significantly.</li>
        <li><strong>Recharts over D3/Chart.js</strong> — React-native chart library with composable components.</li>
        <li><strong>Axios over fetch</strong> — Interceptors for auth token injection and 401 handling.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

