  <!-- Tab: Directus -->
  <div class="tab-content" id="tab-directus">
    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p><strong>Directus</strong> is an open-source headless CMS that wraps PostgreSQL with a REST API, GraphQL, and an admin panel. In this project, Directus serves as the data persistence layer — it stores all records, manages relationships, handles user authentication, and provides the admin interface for schema configuration and data browsing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>How to Run</h2>
      <pre><code>docker compose up -d directus  # starts Directus on port 9000 (depends on postgres)
# Admin panel: http://localhost:9000/admin
# Login with ADMIN_EMAIL / ADMIN_PASSWORD from .env</code></pre>
      <p>First-time startup may take 30–60 seconds for Directus to run its migration scripts. Container health check polls <code>/server/health</code> until ready.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Collections</h2>
      <p>Each collection is created manually through the Directus admin panel. The backend service account (identified by <code>DIRECTUS_TOKEN</code>) needs full CRUD permissions on all <code>items/*</code> endpoints.</p>
      <table>
        <tr><th>Collection</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Key Relationships</th></tr>
        <tr><td><code>students</code></td><td>Student profiles</td><td>M2O → class_streams</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>subjects</code></td><td>Academic subjects</td><td>M2M → class_streams via class_subjects</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>class_streams</code></td><td>Class streams/grades</td><td>O2M → students, M2M → subjects</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>assessments</code></td><td>Exam and CA scores</td><td>M2O → students, M2O → subjects</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>attendance</code></td><td>Daily attendance records</td><td>M2O → students, M2O → class_streams</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>grading_scale</code></td><td>Grade boundaries</td><td>No relations</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>system_logs</code></td><td>Audit trail</td><td>M2O → directus_users</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>directus_users</code></td><td>User accounts</td><td>JSON assignedClasses for teachers</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Permissions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Backend service token</strong> — Full access to all <code>items/*</code> CRUD. Set as <code>DIRECTUS_TOKEN</code> in <code>.env</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Admin users</strong> — Access via Express backend. Can view all classes, manage users, CRUD subjects/classes.</li>
        <li><strong>Teacher users</strong> — Scoped to assigned classes via <code>assignedClasses</code> JSON array on <code>directus_users</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Role field</strong> — Stored as string (<code>admin</code>, <code>teacher</code>, <code>pending</code>). New signups default to <code>pending</code>.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Tech Decisions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Directus over Strapi</strong> — More mature admin panel, better PostgreSQL support, simpler permission model.</li>
        <li><strong>Directus over Sanity/Contentful</strong> — Self-hosted, no per-seat licensing, full control over schema and backups.</li>
        <li><strong>Directus over custom CRUD code</strong> — Eliminates writing CRUD endpoints, migration scripts, and admin panel.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>External Links</h2>
      <a class="ext-link" href="https://docs.directus.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><i data-lucide="external-link" style="width:14px;height:14px"></i> Directus Docs</a>
      <a class="ext-link" href="https://docs.directus.io/reference/system/tokens.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><i data-lucide="external-link" style="width:14px;height:14px"></i> API Tokens</a>
