      <a class="ext-link" href="https://docs.directus.io/reference/system/permissions.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><i data-lucide="external-link" style="width:14px;height:14px"></i> Permissions</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Tab: PostgreSQL -->
  <div class="tab-content" id="tab-postgresql">
    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>PostgreSQL 16 runs in a Docker container. The schema is managed entirely by Directus — collections and fields are created through the Directus admin interface, which auto-generates the underlying PostgreSQL tables, indexes, and relationships.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>How to Run</h2>
      <pre><code>docker compose up -d postgres  # starts PostgreSQL on port 5432
# Directus auto-migrates schema on startup</code></pre>
      <p>Connection settings are configured via environment variables: <code>DB_HOST</code>, <code>DB_PORT</code>, <code>DB_DATABASE</code>, <code>DB_USER</code>, <code>DB_PASSWORD</code>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Schema Overview</h2>
      <table>
        <tr><th>Collection</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Key Fields</th></tr>
        <tr><td><code>students</code></td><td>Student profiles</td><td>admissionNumber (unique), classStreamId (M2O)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>subjects</code></td><td>Academic subjects</td><td>name, code (unique), isActive</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>class_streams</code></td><td>Class streams</td><td>name, code (unique), description</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>class_subjects</code></td><td>Junction table</td><td>classStreamId (M2O), subjectId (M2O)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>assessments</code></td><td>Exam/CA scores</td><td>type (exam|continuous_assessment), score, term, academicYear</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>attendance</code></td><td>Daily attendance</td><td>date, status (present|absent), term, academicYear, isLastDay</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>grading_scale</code></td><td>Grade boundaries</td><td>grade (A/B/C/F), lowerBound, upperBound, gradePoint</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>system_logs</code></td><td>Audit trail</td><td>action, description, level (info|warn|error)</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Tech Decisions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>PostgreSQL over MySQL</strong> — Better JSON support (used for <code>assignedClasses</code> array), superior indexing, full-text search, robust concurrent transactions.</li>
        <li><strong>PostgreSQL over MongoDB</strong> — Highly relational data (students ↔ classes, assessments ↔ students/subjects). Document store would require manual joins and consistency management.</li>
        <li><strong>Schema managed by Directus</strong> — Eliminates standalone migration scripts. Schema changes made through Directus UI and auto-applied to PostgreSQL.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>External Links</h2>
      <a class="ext-link" href="https://www.postgresql.org/docs/16/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><i data-lucide="external-link" style="width:14px;height:14px"></i> PostgreSQL 16 Docs</a>
      <a class="ext-link" href="https://www.postgresql.org/docs/16/datatype-json.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><i data-lucide="external-link" style="width:14px;height:14px"></i> JSON Types</a>
      <a class="ext-link" href="https://www.postgresql.org/docs/16/indexes.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><i data-lucide="external-link" style="width:14px;height:14px"></i> Indexes</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Tab: Architecture -->
  <div class="tab-content" id="tab-architecture">
    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>System Design</h2>
      <p>The system runs as four Docker containers orchestrated by Docker Compose:</p>
      <pre><code>┌──────────┐     ┌──────────┐     ┌──────────┐     ┌──────────┐
│ Frontend │────▶│ Backend  │────▶│ Directus │────▶│PostgreSQL│
│ :9001    │     │ :9002    │     │ :9000    │     │ :5432    │
└──────────┘     └──────────┘     └──────────┘     └──────────┘</code></pre>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Frontend</strong> (Nginx, serving Vite-built static files) — Reverse proxies <code>/api/*</code> to backend</li>
        <li><strong>Backend</strong> (Node.js + Express) — Business logic, auth, PDF generation</li>
        <li><strong>Directus</strong> (PHP + Node.js) — Data API, admin panel, file uploads</li>
        <li><strong>PostgreSQL</strong> — Single database for Directus and all application data</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Data Flow</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Browser</strong> loads the React SPA from the frontend container</li>
        <li><strong>User action</strong> triggers API call through a typed client module</li>
        <li><strong>Axios client</strong> attaches JWT Bearer token, sends request to <code>/api/...</code></li>
        <li><strong>Vite dev proxy</strong> (or Nginx in production) forwards to backend</li>
        <li><strong>Express middleware</strong> verifies JWT, sets <code>req.user</code></li>
        <li><strong>Controller</strong> builds Directus filter, calls Directus service</li>
        <li><strong>Directus service</strong> makes authenticated request to Directus REST API</li>
        <li><strong>Directus</strong> queries PostgreSQL, applies permissions, returns results</li>
        <li><strong>Controller</strong> normalizes response, applies business logic, returns JSON</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
      <h2>Deployment</h2>
      <p>All services deployed via <strong>Docker Compose</strong>. Key considerations:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Secrets:</strong> <code>JWT_SECRET</code>, <code>DIRECTUS_TOKEN</code>, <code>DIRECTUS_KEY</code>, <code>DIRECTUS_SECRET</code>, <code>DB_PASSWORD</code> must be changed from defaults in production</li>
        <li><strong>Persistence:</strong> PostgreSQL data in named Docker volume (<code>pgdata</code>). Directus uploads and extensions use separate volumes</li>
        <li><strong>Health checks:</strong> Each container has a health check. Docker Compose uses <code>depends_on</code> with <code>condition: service_healthy</code></li>
        <li><strong>Resource limits:</strong> 512MB for PostgreSQL and Directus, 256MB for backend, 128MB for frontend</li>
        <li><strong>Networking:</strong> Internal Docker network. Exposed ports: 9000 (Directus admin), 9001 (Frontend), 9002 (Backend API)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

